WEBVTT

00:00.002 --> 00:01.401
<i>Hi I'm Chuck.</i>
<i>And here's what's</i>

00:01.407 --> 00:02.377
<i>been going on</i>
<i>in my life lately.</i>

00:03.526 --> 00:04.630
This is a not

00:04.667 --> 00:05.670
a real attack, is it?

00:05.704 --> 00:06.873
No, this is our competition.

00:06.908 --> 00:08.981
Verbanski Corp took all
of our clients.

00:09.015 --> 00:10.419
Told you.
You put me out there,

00:10.453 --> 00:11.656
you don't have
to worry

00:11.692 --> 00:12.827
about what other
companies are doing.

00:12.861 --> 00:13.728
Morgan needs a handler.

00:13.762 --> 00:14.562
What? Who, me?

00:14.597 --> 00:17.138
You be my handler. Yeah!

00:17.173 --> 00:18.745
Just because you have
the Intersect in you

00:18.779 --> 00:20.513
doesn't mean you don't have
something to learn still!

00:20.547 --> 00:21.914
I have something
I can offer you

00:21.949 --> 00:23.049
no one else can.

00:25.000 --> 00:31.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:35.896 --> 00:36.896
Okay, target acquired.

00:36.930 --> 00:39.432
Distance to intercept:
100 meters.

00:39.466 --> 00:41.834
This is it. You ready, Casey?

00:41.869 --> 00:44.837
Readiness-- like life--

00:44.855 --> 00:46.439
begins at the point
of conception.

00:46.473 --> 00:47.807
Where am I headed?

00:47.841 --> 00:49.776
Other side of the street.
You should be hitting a one-way.

00:49.810 --> 00:51.878
Head south
to initiate intercept.

00:51.912 --> 00:53.312
Roger that.

00:53.347 --> 00:55.548
You okay? Your blood pressure
just went through the roof.

00:56.700 --> 00:58.551
I'm fine.

00:58.585 --> 00:59.685
How much time till intercept?

00:59.720 --> 01:02.038
Steady. In five,

01:02.072 --> 01:03.923
four, three,

01:03.957 --> 01:05.958
two, one.

01:07.077 --> 01:08.411
John!

01:08.462 --> 01:10.079
Gertrude, hey.

01:10.130 --> 01:12.365
What are the chances?

01:12.399 --> 01:13.533
Her favorite restaurant is

01:13.567 --> 01:16.886
a block away,
a raw bar called Cerulean.

01:16.920 --> 01:20.106
I was just, uh,
going around the corner

01:20.140 --> 01:21.441
to that little oyster bar.

01:21.475 --> 01:24.811
Cerulean-- that... that is
my favorite restaurant.

01:24.845 --> 01:26.112
What are the chances?

01:27.147 --> 01:28.581
Wow!

01:28.615 --> 01:30.283
You know, I could really go

01:30.317 --> 01:32.051
for some Blue Points
right about now.

01:32.069 --> 01:34.120
Did you hear that?

01:34.154 --> 01:35.238
The target is yours.
Ask her out.

01:35.272 --> 01:36.856
She practically
just asked you out.

01:36.890 --> 01:38.658
Blue Points are delicious.

01:38.692 --> 01:40.993
Especially with a little
mignonette sauce.

01:41.028 --> 01:43.062
Boy, that's
the best thing

01:43.097 --> 01:45.131
the damn French ever gave us.

01:46.533 --> 01:48.501
Come on, Casey.

01:49.937 --> 01:53.773
Well, it was great
talking to you.

01:53.807 --> 01:56.309
No, wait! Just give a kiss
on the cheek.

01:56.343 --> 01:58.511
Just let her know you're
available and interested!

01:59.980 --> 02:01.347
I guess I'll, uh,

02:01.381 --> 02:02.765
see you around?

02:02.800 --> 02:04.433
Come on!

02:04.468 --> 02:05.852
Yes...

02:12.392 --> 02:13.726
So you froze up.

02:13.760 --> 02:15.862
It happens
to the best of us.

02:15.896 --> 02:17.597
No, I didn't freeze.

02:17.631 --> 02:18.931
Then what do
you call that?

02:18.966 --> 02:20.032
Reconnaissance.

02:20.067 --> 02:22.318
Wait. You planted a bug
on Verbanski?

02:22.369 --> 02:25.872
Mm-hmm. Piggybacks off
her cell phone's Wi-Fi.

02:25.906 --> 02:27.473
That's a weird
move, Casey.

02:27.508 --> 02:29.575
This way I can find out
everything I need to

02:29.610 --> 02:31.077
before I ask her out.

02:31.111 --> 02:33.379
I'm pretty sure that's why
people go on dates,

02:33.413 --> 02:35.581
to get to know one another.
Just do me a favor,

02:35.616 --> 02:37.316
don't tell Chuck
and Morgan about it.

02:37.351 --> 02:38.551
Lips are sealed.

02:41.839 --> 02:46.342
How many triple words are
you gonna leave open, Jeff?

02:46.393 --> 02:47.960
My God, he's dumb.

02:47.995 --> 02:48.828
Morgan...

02:48.862 --> 02:50.029
Boom! 87 points, huh?!

02:50.063 --> 02:51.597
It's good to be
the Intersect.

02:51.632 --> 02:53.132
Please, buddy,
we're on a mission.

02:53.167 --> 02:54.967
Oh, right. Sorry.

02:55.002 --> 02:57.370
I thought we were just sitting
in some Burbank parking garage.

02:57.404 --> 02:59.906
Oh, I'm sorry, you got
somewhere you need to be?

02:59.940 --> 03:01.674
I have a hot date.
No biggie.

03:01.708 --> 03:03.042
If this is how you choose

03:03.076 --> 03:04.851
to use the world's greatest
super-computer. Well...

03:04.852 --> 03:08.418
Okay, okay, this is
actually what I needed

03:08.949 --> 03:10.049
Hmm?
to talk to you about.

03:10.083 --> 03:12.118
Um, the attitude.

03:12.152 --> 03:14.020
Am I not the world's
greatest...?

03:14.054 --> 03:15.688
Being the Intersect doesn't mean
you have to constantly talk

03:15.722 --> 03:16.856
about being the Intersect.

03:16.890 --> 03:19.192
You did it your way,
I'll do it my way.

03:19.226 --> 03:21.761
- Morgan!
- Chuck!

03:21.795 --> 03:23.296
I hate to say it, buddy,

03:23.330 --> 03:24.830
but you're starting
to remind me

03:24.865 --> 03:26.499
of seventh-grade Morgan,
and I think

03:26.533 --> 03:28.334
we both know
what happened to him.

03:31.605 --> 03:33.139
Stay here.

03:35.576 --> 03:36.609
Got it, boss.

03:42.149 --> 03:44.183
It's good to see you again.

03:44.218 --> 03:46.252
I trust you
and your team are well?

03:46.286 --> 03:47.853
Hanging in there, yeah.

03:47.888 --> 03:50.556
Turns out working in
the private sector is...

03:50.591 --> 03:52.892
Look, I think it's better
if we keep this brief.

03:52.926 --> 03:54.927
No offense.

03:54.962 --> 03:57.463
You've heard of Mats Zorn?

03:57.497 --> 03:59.398
Yeah, rich guy with
the whistleblower Web site?

03:59.433 --> 04:02.134
Makes WikiLeaks look like
child's play.

04:02.169 --> 04:04.370
A number of classified
CIA memos have fallen

04:04.388 --> 04:05.805
into Zorn's hands.

04:05.839 --> 04:07.540
So, you want us to grab Zorn?

04:07.574 --> 04:09.141
And the documents.

04:09.176 --> 04:10.543
The drive contains
his itinerary.

04:10.577 --> 04:12.144
Zorn doesn't stay
in one place

04:12.179 --> 04:13.646
any longer than
it takes refuel,

04:13.680 --> 04:15.114
but we have him
passing through L.A.

04:15.148 --> 04:16.882
This is a paying gig, right?

04:16.916 --> 04:18.985
There's a sizeable
bounty on Zorn.

04:19.019 --> 04:20.920
I'm outsourcing to your team
to circumvent the leak.

04:20.954 --> 04:23.723
My only condition is
that no one breathes my name

04:23.757 --> 04:24.724
in relation
to the mission.

04:26.360 --> 04:28.060
Yo, Becky!

04:28.095 --> 04:30.630
What up, baby girl?

04:30.664 --> 04:32.198
I told you to come alone.

04:32.232 --> 04:34.800
You doing Pilates, huh? You are,
don't say you're not. You are.

04:34.835 --> 04:36.669
What the hell is wrong with him?

04:36.703 --> 04:38.838
So many things.

04:38.872 --> 04:40.640
Becky, your core's really tight.

04:47.130 --> 04:49.181
Alex?

04:49.216 --> 04:50.182
Oh, hey.

04:50.217 --> 04:51.917
I thought you were Morgan.

04:51.952 --> 04:54.120
No, I just dropped
him off at the Buy More.

04:54.154 --> 04:55.221
What?

04:55.255 --> 04:57.456
Guess he forgot about our plans.

04:57.491 --> 04:58.624
I wouldn't say that.

04:58.659 --> 05:00.693
I mean, he did mention
having a hot date, so...

05:00.727 --> 05:04.297
Well, clearly it's
with someone else.

05:04.331 --> 05:06.799
Is there something going on
between you two?

05:06.833 --> 05:11.437
You would tell me if Morgan's
seeing someone else, right?

05:11.471 --> 05:16.108
Yes. And no, he is not.

05:16.143 --> 05:19.178
He's had a lot on his mind
lately, that's all.

05:19.212 --> 05:21.447
Let me track him down and talk
some sense into him, okay?

05:21.481 --> 05:23.449
Okay.

05:23.467 --> 05:24.317
Chin up.

05:24.351 --> 05:25.785
Thanks.

05:31.458 --> 05:33.659
Oh, hey. How'd it go
with the general?

05:33.694 --> 05:35.177
Piece of cake.

05:35.228 --> 05:37.730
Data drive with the mission's
locked up tight in Castle.

05:37.764 --> 05:39.799
- So what's the problem?
- Morgan.

05:39.833 --> 05:42.301
I tried to have
a heart-to-heart with him

05:42.336 --> 05:44.670
about his...
Overblown ego?

05:44.705 --> 05:46.038
Anyway, he went AWOL.

05:46.073 --> 05:48.641
Casey, can you can help
with a surveillance detail?

05:50.744 --> 05:51.711
Casey, what you looking at?

05:51.745 --> 05:52.845
Nothing.
None of your business.

05:52.879 --> 05:54.980
Ooh, you got a wire up on
someone, huh?

05:55.015 --> 05:56.282
Who is it?

05:56.316 --> 05:57.550
Verbanski.

05:57.584 --> 05:59.318
Corporate espionage.
He's just sizing up

05:59.353 --> 06:00.686
the competition,
that's all.

06:00.721 --> 06:01.987
Perving out on Gertrude.

06:02.022 --> 06:03.389
Weird move, Casey.

06:03.423 --> 06:04.657
I told you.

06:04.691 --> 06:07.860
So, have you
considered my offer?

06:07.894 --> 06:09.661
Gertrude, do me a favor.

06:09.679 --> 06:11.997
What is he doing
in her office?

06:12.015 --> 06:13.599
That's a good question.

06:13.633 --> 06:16.385
Next time you make me an offer
like that to me,

06:16.436 --> 06:18.837
why don't you go ahead and spit
in my face instead?

06:18.855 --> 06:19.872
Thank you, Morgan.

06:21.208 --> 06:22.558
Bubala...

06:22.609 --> 06:26.512
I offer you the services
of the world's greatest spy,

06:26.530 --> 06:28.948
and you don't have
the decency,

06:28.982 --> 06:31.784
the common courtesy
to offer me my own...

06:31.818 --> 06:34.754
personal assistant?

06:35.789 --> 06:36.855
Bush league.

06:36.873 --> 06:39.692
You drive a hard bargain,
Mr. Grimes.

06:39.726 --> 06:41.360
Yeah, I try.

06:43.663 --> 06:45.714
Welcome to Verbanski Corp.

06:50.003 --> 06:51.203
You little...

06:51.238 --> 06:52.772
...traitor.

06:52.806 --> 06:55.057
I'm gonna like it here.

